00:03:11.230 --> 00:03:14.300
 at how deep the community

00:03:14.300 --> 00:03:17.570
becomes through the online platform.

00:03:17.570 --> 00:03:20.940
So the first thing they do is they come
together and we have these

00:03:20.940 --> 00:03:24.800
intense experiential sessions for
almost two weeks together.

00:03:24.800 --> 00:03:28.690
Two courses. And they bond. Students all
get to know each other.  They get to know the

00:03:28.690 --> 00:03:30.890
program. They get to know us. They get to  know Naropa

00:03:30.890 --> 00:03:34.040
and then by the time they go out online they all know each other and then when the

00:03:34.040 --> 00:03:35.120
voices come in

00:03:35.120 --> 00:03:39.200
as written form -- its like oh that's this
person. I'm so glad to know that's what

00:03:39.200 --> 00:03:40.200
they're thinking.

00:03:40.200 --> 00:03:44.850
We are working to develop community among the students

00:03:44.850 --> 00:03:48.260
and community with the faculty.  And community with the land.

00:03:48.260 --> 00:03:52.770
In our first summer intensives we spend
time outdoors.

00:03:52.770 --> 00:03:58.459
By the second summer intensive, students
are doing a week-long wilderness

00:03:58.459 --> 00:04:01.540
immersion course -- essentially a right

00:04:01.540 --> 00:04:05.170
of passage. And these 

00:04:05.170 --> 00:04:08.320
students tell us after they graduate are

00:04:08.320 --> 00:04:11.540
some of the most important moments

00:04:11.540 --> 00:04:14.980
in the whole program. Our students are
amazing!

00:04:14.980 --> 00:04:18.090
These are people who recognize that
the world is

00:04:18.090 --> 00:04:21.340
in crisis and they are impassioned to do
something about it.

00:04:21.340 --> 00:04:25.190
They want to understand what's going on
and they want to help it be better.

00:04:25.190 --> 00:04:32.190
And it's a great privilege to work with
people like that. ♫ ♫

